Functionality of Decimal to Fraction Converter

Overview

The "Decimal to Fraction Converter" program takes a decimal number entered by the user and converts it into a fraction. It utilizes the Python fractions library to perform this conversion.
Prerequisites

Before using this program, ensure that you have Python installed on your system. Additionally, no external dependencies are required as the program uses Python's standard library fractions.
Installation

No special installation is required for this program since it utilizes Python's standard libraries. Just make sure that Python is installed on your system.
Usage

To use the program, follow these steps:

    Run the program in your preferred Python environment.
    Enter a decimal number when prompted.
    The program will convert the entered decimal into a fraction.
    It will display both the original decimal and the equivalent fraction.
    You can repeat the process as many times as you like or exit the program when you wish.
